properties.Name: ExperianCreditReport
properties.Description:
A Experian (TRW) Credit Report, which is a summary of a consumer's recent credit history plus additional facts about the consumer that will help creditors judge the consumer's creditworthiness.

TRW/FICO Model: This scoring system developed by TRW in association with Fair, Isaac, and Company, Inc. The score enables credit grantor to identify credit prospect with the best credit opportunities and avoid losses due to charge-offs, repossessions, collections, and bankruptcies.

Columns.Name: ExperianReportNumber
Columns.Description: The unique identifier of an Experian consumer.

Columns.Name: ReportDate
Columns.Description: The report date of the Credit Report.

Columns.Name: ExperianConsumerId
Columns.Description: The unique identifier of an Experian consumer.

Columns.Name: SecurityFreezeIndicator
Columns.Description: A security freeze will prevent Experian from releasing your credit information without your express authorization.

Columns.Name: CustomerId
Columns.Description: The unique identifier of a Customer.

Columns.Name: TotalNumberOfAccounts
Columns.Description: The total number of all accounts.

Columns.Name: TotalBalanceAmount
Columns.Description: The total balance amount of all accounts.

Columns.Name: TotalDelinquentAmount
Columns.Description: The total delinquent amount of all accounts.

Columns.Name: TotalOpenAccounts
Columns.Description: The total number of open accounts.

Columns.Name: TotalClosedAccounts
Columns.Description: The total number of closed accounts.

Columns.Name: NumberOfPublicRecords
Columns.Description: The number of public records associated with the consumer.

Columns.Name: NumberOfInquiriesPrevious6Months
Columns.Description: The number of inquiries within the last 6 months.
